	)
	(text "STM - INPUT\nVREF+ = 3.3V \n\nACS VIOUT - OUTPUT: \nVIOUT = 5VMAX\n5/2 = 2.5V \nMAX I = +-2.5\nSENSITIVITY: 800mV/A\n\nVIOUT_MAX = 2.5 + 2.5*800mA = 4.5v\nVIOUT_NO_Meassurement = vdd/2 = 2.5V\nVIOUT_MIN = 2.5 - 2.5*800mA = 0.5v\n4.5V > THEN 3.3V => DOWN SCALLING NECESARRY\n\nDOWN SCALLING by 1/2:\nVIOUT_MAX = 2.25\n0V = 2.5/2 = 1.25V\nVIOUT_MIN = 0.25\n\n\nOVER VOLTAGE PROTECTION\nTHIS MAY BE NECESARY IF THE CURRENT EXEEDS THE LIMITS O +-2.5V\nTHIS WOULD BRING THE ADC PIN ON STM32 ABOVE 3.3V PIN VOLTAGE LIMIT\nAND CAUSE DAMAGE.\n\nCOMPARATOR + MOSFET would do. \n\nIn this case the situation is much simpler: \nfirstly, LPS is done tHrough filter pin. \nsecondly, max VOUTI is 5V limitted by VCC, \nby implementing 1/2 divider, the 3v3 capable pin will never exceed 2.5V.\n\nCONVERSION TIME\nThe conversion time of the adc on the stm32 is very capable. \nThis can be, however, limited by the RC constant introduced on the ADC input line.\nMainly by dividers and stray capacitance, or by LPF. \n\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at -133.096 -46.228 0)
